amid /əˈmɪd/

1. PREP If something happens amid noises or events of some kind, it happens while the other things are happening. 在…当中 

例： Workers are sifting through the wreckage of the airliners amid growing evidence that the disasters were the work of terrorists. 在越来越多证据证明这些灾难是恐怖分子所为的同时，工人们正在仔细检查那些客机的残骸。

